<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8"/>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Automote — Case Study · Paige</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Serif+Display:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,300;0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;1,9..40,300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="hunza-case-study.css">
  <style>
    .cs-hero-bg {
      background: linear-gradient(160deg, #0f1a2e 0%, #0a0a08 65%);
    }
    .cs-hero-bg::after {
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 65% 30%, rgba(80,120,200,0.1) 0%, transparent 55%);
    }

    /* Screenshots side by side */
    .screens-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1.5rem;
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    .screen-panel {}
    .screen-panel-label {
      font-size: 0.63rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.16em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: rgba(246,243,238,0.35);
      margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .screen-panel-label span {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 0.12rem 0.5rem;
      border-radius: 100px;
      font-size: 0.58rem;
      background: rgba(80,120,200,0.15);
      color: rgba(130,160,255,0.8);
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    }
    .screen-panel img {
      width: 100%;
      border-radius: 8px;
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
      display: block;
      transition: transform 0.4s ease, box-shadow 0.4s ease;
    }
    .screen-panel img:hover {
      transform: scale(1.02);
      box-shadow: 0 20px 60px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
    }
    .screen-panel-cap {
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      color: rgba(246,243,238,0.3);
      margin-top: 0.7rem;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    /* Pain points — annotated list */
    .pain-list {
      list-style: none;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .pain-item {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: auto 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
      padding: 1.2rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
      align-items: start;
    }
    .pain-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); }
    .pain-num {
      font-family: var(--serif);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: rgba(80,120,200,0.5);
      width: 2rem;
      flex-shrink: 0;
      padding-top: 1px;
    }
    .pain-text strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.88rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--white);
      margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    }
    .pain-text p {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: rgba(246,243,238,0.5);
    }

    /* Solution cards */
    .solution-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .sol {
      background: rgba(80,120,200,0.06);
      border: 1px solid rgba(80,120,200,0.15);
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 1.6rem;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .sol::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0;
      height: 2px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(80,120,200,0.6), transparent);
    }
    .sol-icon {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
      display: block;
    }
    .sol-t {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 500;
      color: var(--white);
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    }
    .sol-b {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: rgba(246,243,238,0.5);
    }

    /* Before/after comparison pill */
    .compare-wrap {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
      align-items: center;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .compare-col {
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
      border-radius: 4px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
    .compare-col--after {
      background: rgba(80,120,200,0.06);
      border-color: rgba(80,120,200,0.18);
    }
    .compare-label {
      font-size: 0.6rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      display: block;
    }
    .compare-label--before { color: rgba(246,243,238,0.3); }
    .compare-label--after { color: rgba(130,160,255,0.8); }
    .compare-item {
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: rgba(246,243,238,0.5);
      padding: 0.3rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    .compare-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .compare-item::before { content: '—'; color: rgba(246,243,238,0.2); flex-shrink: 0; }
    .compare-col--after .compare-item::before { content: '✓'; color: rgba(130,160,255,0.7); }
    .compare-arrow {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.4rem;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 0.6rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .screens-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .solution-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .compare-wrap { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .compare-arrow { flex-direction: row; padding: 0.5rem 0; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <nav>
    <a href="index.html" class="nav-logo">Paige.</a>
    <a href="index.html#work" class="nav-back">
      <svg width="16" height="12" viewBox="0 0 16 12" fill="none">
        <path d="M15 6H1M7 1L1 6l6 5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
      </svg>
      All work
    </a>
  </nav>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="cs-hero">
    <div class="cs-hero-bg"></div>
    <div class="cs-hero-top">
      <span class="cs-eyebrow">Case Study — B2B UX/UI · Desktop App Redesign</span>
      <span class="cs-year">2022 – 2023 · LuminateOne Internship</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cs-hero-content">
      <h1 class="cs-title">
        <span class="cs-title-line">Automote —</span>
        <span class="cs-title-line">Built for dealers.</span>
      </h1>
      <div class="cs-hero-meta">
        <div><p class="cs-meta-label">My Role</p><p class="cs-meta-value">UX/UI Redesign (Figma)</p></div>
        <div><p class="cs-meta-label">Client</p><p class="cs-meta-value">LuminateOne · Automotive</p></div>
        <div><p class="cs-meta-label">Users</p><p class="cs-meta-value">Car Dealership Staff</p></div>
        <div><p class="cs-meta-label">Output</p><p class="cs-meta-value">Fully Interactive Figma Prototype</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- 01 Overview -->
  <section class="cs-section">
    <div class="inner">
      <div class="two-col">
        <div>
          <span class="section-label">01 — Overview</span>
          <h2 class="section-heading">A tool used every day by car dealers — that made their jobs harder.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="body-text">
          <p>During my internship at <strong>LuminateOne</strong>, I was tasked with redesigning Automote — a stock and inventory management platform used daily by car dealership staff to manage orders, configure vehicle builds, and track inventory across their dealership.</p>
          <p>The existing interface had accumulated years of technical debt and band-aid fixes. The result was a tool that was genuinely <strong>painful to use</strong> — text and buttons cut off mid-screen, navigation that required too many clicks, weak or missing feedback states, and a layout that fell apart on anything other than a single screen size.</p>
          <p>I redesigned the platform end-to-end in Figma, producing a <strong>fully interactive prototype</strong> covering the core dealer workflows.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 02 Final output -->
  <section class="cs-section">
    <div class="inner">
      <span class="section-label">02 — Final Design</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">The redesigned platform.</h2>
      <div class="screens-grid">
        <div class="screen-panel">
          <p class="screen-panel-label">Orders <span>Order Management</span></p>
          <img src="automote-orders.png" alt="Automote orders screen — redesigned"/>
          <p class="screen-panel-cap">The orders view — filterable by ID, customer, model, date, and production status. Clear hierarchy, consistent actions, and a status system that actually communicates where each order is.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="screen-panel">
          <p class="screen-panel-label">Configure Builds <span>Vehicle Configuration</span></p>
          <img src="automote-configure.png" alt="Automote configure builds screen — redesigned"/>
          <p class="screen-panel-cap">The build configurator — dealers set up vehicle specs (trim levels, battery size, interior, drive train) with a two-panel layout that keeps details and configuration steps in view simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 03 Problem -->
  <section class="cs-section">
    <div class="inner">
      <span class="section-label">03 — The Problem</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Six problems that made a hard job harder.</h2>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="body-text">
          <p>Dealership staff use Automote for hours every day — managing dozens of orders, tracking vehicles through production pipelines, and configuring complex build options for customers. <strong>Every friction point in the UI compounds across hundreds of interactions.</strong></p>
          <p>I audited the existing platform and identified six core failure points that were consistently slowing users down or causing errors.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="pain-list">
          <li class="pain-item">
            <span class="pain-num">01</span>
            <div class="pain-text">
              <strong>Text and buttons cut off</strong>
              <p>UI elements were truncated at screen edges — labels, CTAs, and data values disappearing mid-character with no overflow handling.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pain-item">
            <span class="pain-num">02</span>
            <div class="pain-text">
              <strong>Complex, unintuitive navigation</strong>
              <p>Too many clicks to reach common actions. Hierarchy was flat and unlabelled — users had to memorise where things lived rather than discover them.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pain-item">
            <span class="pain-num">03</span>
            <div class="pain-text">
              <strong>Weak or absent CTAs</strong>
              <p>Primary actions weren't visually distinguished from secondary ones. Buttons lacked weight, colour, and hierarchy — making it unclear what to do next.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pain-item">
            <span class="pain-num">04</span>
            <div class="pain-text">
              <strong>No system feedback</strong>
              <p>Actions completed silently — no confirmation, no error states, no loading indicators. Users couldn't tell if something had worked or failed.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pain-item">
            <span class="pain-num">05</span>
            <div class="pain-text">
              <strong>Poor responsiveness</strong>
              <p>The layout was built for one fixed screen size. On any other display — wider monitors, smaller laptops — components collapsed or overlapped unpredictably.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="pain-item">
            <span class="pain-num">06</span>
            <div class="pain-text">
              <strong>Inconsistent visual language</strong>
              <p>No design system. Spacing, type sizes, button styles, and colour usage varied across screens — making the platform feel unfinished and hard to trust.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 04 Before vs After -->
  <section class="cs-section">
    <div class="inner">
      <span class="section-label">04 — Before vs After</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">What changed and why.</h2>
      <div class="compare-wrap">
        <div class="compare-col">
          <span class="compare-label compare-label--before">Before — existing platform</span>
          <div class="compare-item">Truncated text and clipped buttons throughout</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Flat navigation with no clear hierarchy</div>
          <div class="compare-item">No visual distinction between primary and secondary actions</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Silent actions — no feedback on success or failure</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Fixed layout, broken on non-standard screens</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Inconsistent spacing, type, and colour across screens</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Dense, unstructured data tables</div>
        </div>
        <div class="compare-arrow">
          <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
            <path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
          Redesigned
        </div>
        <div class="compare-col compare-col--after">
          <span class="compare-label compare-label--after">After — redesigned</span>
          <div class="compare-item">Proper overflow handling, full labels visible at all sizes</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Structured sidebar nav with clear section grouping</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Strong primary CTAs with clear visual weight and hierarchy</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Status indicators, confirmation states, and error messaging</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Fluid layout designed for varied screen sizes</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Unified design system — consistent spacing, type scale, colour</div>
          <div class="compare-item">Scannable tables with filterable columns and sort controls</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 05 Solutions -->
  <section class="cs-section">
    <div class="inner">
      <span class="section-label">05 — Design Decisions</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">The key calls I made.</h2>
      <div class="solution-grid">
        <div class="sol">
          <span class="sol-icon">🗂</span>
          <p class="sol-t">Two-panel layout</p>
          <p class="sol-b">The configure builds screen splits details and configuration steps into a persistent two-panel layout — removing the need to navigate back and forth mid-task.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sol">
          <span class="sol-icon">🔍</span>
          <p class="sol-t">Contextual filters</p>
          <p class="sol-b">The orders view uses a collapsible side filter panel — visible when needed, out of the way when not. Filters by ID, customer, model, date range, and production status.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sol">
          <span class="sol-icon">🚦</span>
          <p class="sol-t">Status as communication</p>
          <p class="sol-b">Production status and system status are displayed as clear text labels, not icons or colour alone — making the system readable at a glance without requiring legend lookup.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sol">
          <span class="sol-icon">⚓</span>
          <p class="sol-t">Anchored navigation</p>
          <p class="sol-b">The sidebar nav groups tools into logical categories (Data Manager, eCommerce, Vehicles) with persistent context — dealers always know where they are and how to get somewhere else.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sol">
          <span class="sol-icon">🎯</span>
          <p class="sol-t">Clear action hierarchy</p>
          <p class="sol-b">Primary actions (Add Progress, Save) use filled buttons with strong colour. Secondary and destructive actions (edit, delete) are iconographic and subdued — reducing accidental actions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sol">
          <span class="sol-icon">📐</span>
          <p class="sol-t">Consistent design system</p>
          <p class="sol-b">Built a unified component system in Figma — consistent spacing scale, type hierarchy, button variants, and form elements — applied across every screen in the prototype.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 06 Process -->
  <section class="cs-section">
    <div class="inner">
      <span class="section-label">06 — Process</span>
      <h2 class="section-heading">How I worked through it.</h2>
      <div class="process">
        <div class="step">
          <p class="step-n">01</p>
          <p class="step-t">Audit</p>
          <div class="step-b"><ul>
            <li>Mapped all existing screens</li>
            <li>Identified and documented every UI failure</li>
            <li>Catalogued inconsistencies</li>
            <li>Prioritised by user impact</li>
          </ul></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <p class="step-n">02</p>
          <p class="step-t">Understand</p>
          <div class="step-b"><ul>
            <li>Mapped core dealer workflows</li>
            <li>Identified high-frequency tasks</li>
            <li>Defined user goals per section</li>
            <li>Noted where current UI blocked them</li>
          </ul></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <p class="step-n">03</p>
          <p class="step-t">Structure</p>
          <div class="step-b"><ul>
            <li>Redesigned information architecture</li>
            <li>Simplified navigation grouping</li>
            <li>Defined layout principles</li>
            <li>Sketched key screen structures</li>
          </ul></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <p class="step-n">04</p>
          <p class="step-t">Design</p>
          <div class="step-b"><ul>
            <li>Built component system in Figma</li>
            <li>Designed all screens high-fidelity</li>
            <li>Applied consistent design language</li>
            <li>Documented usage guidelines</li>
          </ul></div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <p class="step-n">05</p>
          <p class="step-t">Prototype</p>
          <div class="step-b"><ul>
            <li>Fully interactive Figma prototype</li>
            <li>All core workflows connected</li>
            <li>Realistic interactions & transitions</li>
            <li>Presented to LuminateOne team</li>
          </ul></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 07 Reflection -->
  <section class="cs-section">
    <div class="inner">
      <span class="section-label">07 — Reflection</span>
      <div class="reflect-wrap">
        <h2 class="section-heading" style="margin-bottom:0;max-width:none;">Designing for people at work.</h2>
        <div class="reflect-body">
          <blockquote>"B2B design is unforgiving. Consumer apps get forgiven for being confusing — people close them and move on. But a tool you have to use for eight hours a day? Every rough edge costs you something."</blockquote>
          <p>This project taught me that <strong>context of use changes everything.</strong> Dealership staff aren't browsing — they're working under time pressure, often across multiple screens, handling real financial transactions. The cost of confusion isn't frustration, it's mistakes with money and customer relationships on the line.</p>
          <p>The most important lesson: <strong>consistency is a feature.</strong> In a complex tool used daily, predictability reduces cognitive load more than any clever UI trick. Users shouldn't have to think about the interface — they should be thinking about their work.</p>
          <p>Working within an internship context also taught me how to advocate for design decisions clearly — explaining <em>why</em> a change matters in terms stakeholders care about, not just how it looks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="cs-end">
    <div>
      <p class="end-label">Back to portfolio</p>
      <a href="index.html#work" class="end-link">All work →</a>
    </div>
    <a href="index.html#contact" class="end-cta">Get in touch →</a>
  </div>

  <footer>
    <span>© 2026 Paige. All rights reserved.</span>
    <a href="index.html">← Back to portfolio</a>
  </footer>

  <script>
    const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.cs-section');
    const obs = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach(e => {
        if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('visible'); obs.unobserve(e.target); }
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.05 });
    sections.forEach(s => obs.observe(s));
    setTimeout(() => sections.forEach(s => s.classList.add('visible')), 1500);
  </script>
</body>
